This paper discusses a decentralized search engine for the decentralized web, which involves information retrieval (IR) and distributed computing (DC) concepts. It also touches on security issues such as distributed denial-of-service attacks (CR) and tamper-proof contents. Additionally, the paper proposes a new business model for search engines, which could fall under the category of data management (DS) or databases (DB).
